<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-02T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14326:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-02T18:00:00-04:00">September 2, 1941—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>80. For your information, the following is the text of a message from
                                the President to the Shah dated September 2, 1941 in response to a
                                message which the President received from His Majesty. It should
                                also be considered as a response to the message of the Iranian
                                Government transmitted by your 106, August 25, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text of telegram printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>